達成該項基本能力之考評方式Methods Of Evaluating This Ability

1具有以正確流利之英語表達意見、參與討論及溝通之能力Ability to express oneself, discuss and communicate in correct and fluent English.●》方案需求評估2具有以英文書寫學術性摘要、報告及論文之能力Ability to write academic abstracts, reports and papers in English.●》方案需求評估3具有長篇英文文本之閱讀、理解以及對其文化內涵之賞析能力Ability to read and comprehend long English texts and to appreciate their cultural contexts.●》方案需求評估4具備基本口譯、筆譯之能力Ability to engage in preliminary-level translation and interpreting.&nbsp&nbsp5獨立思考，具備提問、討論與解決問題之基本能力Ability to think independently, make inquiries, hold discussions and solve problems.●》團隊參與6通過所學外語之相關能力檢定並具備等同之能力Certification of foreign language proficiency or equal ability.&nbsp&nbsp7廣泛閱讀，提升專業與人文知識Professional and cultural knowledge through extensive reading.●》方案需求評估8具備終身自我學習之概念與實踐能力Ability to undertake life-long, self-directed learning.●》團隊參與9具備創意思考及發展第二專長之能力Ability to think creatively and develop a second specialty.●》實習(含實習心得發表、機構督導評分、學校督導評分等)




二、指定教科書及參考資料 Textbooks and Reference(請修課同學遵守智慧財產權，不得非法影印)


●指定教科書 Required TextsHandout (Mainly taken from An Introduction to Literature (Longman, 12th  and 14th editions) and Norton’s Anthology of Literature by Women)
		●參考書資料暨網路資源 Reference Books and Online Resources


三、教學目標 Objectives


成長小說（教育小說）是小說的重要文類。許多名作家都寫過有關成長經驗的小說或短篇小說，呈現故事中的主角如何經由某個難忘的經驗而得到啟發或感到幻滅，這可以稱為一種象徵性的成長儀式，或靈現。本課程主要閱讀以成長為主題的名家精選短篇故事。藉由閱讀十五到十七篇的短篇小說，透過討論，學生學習思考與分析，並藉由故事中類似的成長經驗而得到啟發。。 


Bildungsroman is an important sub-genre in fiction.  Many famous authors have written novels and stories concerning the experience of growing up to show how a character becomes illuminate d or disillusioned through some unforgettable events, a symbolic rite of passage, or epiphany.  This course will focus on short stories on the theme of growing up.  Students will read 15 to 17 coming-of-age stories and discuss them through reflecting on their own growing up experience. 


四、課程內容 Course Description


●整體敘述 Overall DescriptionThis course will focus on short stories on the theme of growing up.  Students will read 15 to 17 coming-of-age stories and discuss them through individual presentation on the given topics for discussion and through reflections of their own growing up experience.

